<br>
What does everyone think about this?<br>
<br>
Many people think highly of this idea.<br>
<br>
I am a bit skeptical.<br>
<br>
AS a wizard I think highly of ks groups for many reasons.<br>
<br>
now before you start the flaming because I know what you are thinking =)  I got a few arguements to share.<br>
<br>
1.  Ks classes or classes that need less group attention will get the shaft on good groups because they are no longer needed to get exp or no longer needed to be attended to.<br>
<br>
2.  Exp so irrelevant from the raid kills that people will actually miss not getting exp or getting exp in a ks group.<br>
<br>
3.  Competition amongst the high damage classes for the kills makes things die faster.. If this feature goes it.. Whats to prevent people from going afk on the whole raid meaning slower kills and longer raids.<br>
<br>
I like Ks groups.. They add excitement to my class and other classes... Without that added excitement raids will get more tiresome and just plain boring.  Even if I don't get the kill.. It is still exciting to challenge someone else for the kill.. <br>
<br>
I also don't see ks groups as a problem.. If the group organizer took the time to set up fair groups then there would be no or few groups that get too much exp.<br>
<br>
There are other bonuses to using a raid group system but I think the majority of the people who are in support of this is because they want an end to ks groups and more of a share of the exp.<br>
<br>
I assume this feature will be optional but these are still concerns. <p><center>
