<br>
It is more fair.  It's frequently not possible to balance groups so that there isn't one that gets the kill most of the time.  Pull team usually has the toughest job and takes the most risks but they don't always get XP to reward them for their sacrifices and hard work.  If you participate in raid no matter what group you are in, you should share the experience gained from kill.<br>
<br>
Aye, I know you shouldn't worry about XP on raids but people do.   I am tired of people doing stupid things to try to KS or whining about not being able to KS.  I really shouldn't have to tell people to wait for call and not overnuke.  It doesn't happen often but it does happen and most people do know better.  With new system, they won't gain anything from it (and I can kick them out if they don't follow instructions, go AFK too much, or goof off a lot.)<br>
<br>
Assigning looters would make life easier too, especially on epic raids.  I hate having to lock a corpse in order to protect a no drop quest piece.<br>
<br>
